page.title: 04WILDLIFE
page.content: There is a wide range of wildlife due to the situation of the area.Most of the area is uninhabited.Fields and roads are bound by hedges cut back infrequently.The sea and lakeside provide an excellent habitat for a wide range of birds.Some rare birds have been sighted e.g.Grey Phalarope, Snow Eagle.Sea birds include Mute Swan,Mallard,Canada Goose,Heron, Cormorants,Sandpiper,Lapwing, Oystercatcher,Curlew,Water Rail,Tern. Landbirds include-Kestrel,Kite,Buzzard Barn Owl,Pheasant,Cuckoo,Swift,Swallow Dunnock,Redwing,Jay. Animal Life includes-Deer,Rabbit, Badger,Fox,Squirrel,Bat,Vole,Hedgehog, Stoat. Plant Life includes-Campion,Poppy, Meadow Orchid,Honeysuckle,Meadow Vetching,Herb Robert,Hawkbit,Coltsfoot Foxglove,Alder Buckthorn.
